rivet.name: rivet

revisions.description: Modify mibs for VAP, add AuthSupplicantTable and WdsTable

rivet.description: The management information definitions for the 3COM AP-PRIVATE-MIB.

swHardwareVer.name: swHardwareVer
swHardwareVer.description: Hardware version of the main board.

swBootRomVer.name: swBootRomVer
swBootRomVer.description: Boot ROM code version of the main board.

swOpCodeVer.name: swOpCodeVer
swOpCodeVer.description: Operation code version of the main board.

swSerialNumber.name: swSerialNumber
swSerialNumber.description: Serial Number of the Access Point.

lineTable.name: lineTable
lineTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each RS-232 line in this system

lineEntry.name: lineEntry
lineEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one RS232 line of the Access Point.

lineIndex.name: lineIndex
lineIndex.description: This is defined as RS-232 index.

lineDataBits.name: lineDataBits
lineDataBits.description: This is defined as number of data bits for the RS232 interface.

lineParity.name: lineParity
lineParity.description: This is defined as parity of the RS232 interface.

lineSpeed.name: lineSpeed
lineSpeed.description: This is defined as the speed of the RS-232 interface.

lineStopBits.name: lineStopBits
lineStopBits.description: This is defined as the number of stop bits for the RS-232 interface.

portTable.name: portTable
portTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each switch port (including expansion slot) in this system. This table also contains information about each trunk (similar to Cisco's EtherChannel).

portEntry.name: portEntry
portEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one switch port of the switch.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: This is defined as ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

portName.name: portName
portName.description: Indicates the port name. This is same as ifAlias in the IF-MIB (RFC2863 or later).

portSpeedDpxCfg.name: portSpeedDpxCfg
portSpeedDpxCfg.description: Set the port speed and duplex mode as follows: halfDuplex10(2) - 10Mbps and half duplex mode fullDuplex10(3) - 10Mbps and full duplex mode halfDuplex100(4) - 100Mbps and half duplex mode fullDuplex100(5) - 100Mbps and full duplex mode halfDuplex1000(6) - 1000Mbps and half duplex mode fullDuplex1000(7) - 1000Mbps and full duplex mode hundredBaseTX port can be set as halfDuplex10(2) fullDuplex10(3) halfDuplex100(4) fullDuplex100(5) hundredBaseFX port can be set as halfDuplex100(4) fullDuplex100(5) thousandBaseSX port can be set as halfDuplex1000(6) fullDuplex1000(7) The actual operating speed and duplex of the port is given by portSpeedDpxStatus.

portFlowCtrlCfg.name: portFlowCtrlCfg
portFlowCtrlCfg.description: (1) Flow control mechanism is enabled. If the port type is hundredBaseTX or thousandBaseSX: When the port is operating in halfDuplex mode, the port uses backPressure flow control mechanism. When the port is operating in fullDuplex mode, the port uses IEEE 802.3x flow control mechanism. If the port type is hundredBaseFX: When the port is operating in halfDuplex mode, the port uses backPressure flow control mechanism. When the port is operating in fullDuplex mode, Flow control mechanism will not function. (2) Flow control mechanism is disabled. (3) Flow control mechanism is backPressure. when the port is in fullDuplex mode.This flow control mechanism will not function. (4) Flow control mechanism is IEEE 802.3x flow control. when the port is in halfDuplex mode.This flow control mechanism will not function. hundredBaseTX and thousandBaseSX port can be set as: enabled(1), disabled(2), backPressure(3), dot3xFlowControl(4). hundredBaseFX port can be set as: enabled(1), disabled(2), backPressure(3). The actual flow control mechanism is used given by portFlowCtrlStatus.

portSpeedDpxStatus.name: portSpeedDpxStatus
portSpeedDpxStatus.description: The operating speed and duplex mode of the switched port. If this index is a trunk, the speed is the speed of its individual members. If this index is a trunk and the result is inconsistent among its member ports, this value is error(1).

portFlowCtrlStatus.name: portFlowCtrlStatus
portFlowCtrlStatus.description: (2) BackPressure flow control machanism is used. (3) IEEE 802.3 flow control machanism is used. (4) Flow control mechanism is disabled. If this index is a trunk and the result is inconsistent among its member ports, this value is error(1).

srcFile.name: srcFile
srcFile.description: The source file name for TFTP transfer when a transfer is next requested via this MIB. This value is set to the zero length string when no file name has been specified.

destFile.name: destFile
destFile.description: The destination file name for TFTP transfer when a transfer is next requested via this MIB. This value is set to the zero length string when no file name has been specified.

fileServer.name: fileServer
fileServer.description: The IP address of the TFTP server for transfer when a download is next requested via this MIB. This value is set to `0.0.0.0' when no IP address has been specified.

userName.name: userName
userName.description: The username specified for an FTP Transfer.

password.name: password
password.description: The password specified for an FTP Transfer.

restartOpCodeFile.name: restartOpCodeFile
restartOpCodeFile.description: Name of op-code file for start-up.

restartControl.name: restartControl
restartControl.description: Setting this object to warmBoot(2) causes the device to restart the application software with current configuration parameters saved in non-volatile memory. Setting this object to coldBoot(3) causes the device to reinitialize configuration parameters in non-volatile memory to default values and restart the application software. When the device is running normally, this variable has a value of running(1).

netConfigIPAddress.name: netConfigIPAddress
netConfigIPAddress.description: The IP address of this Net interface. The default value for this object is 0.0.0.0. If either the netConfigIPAddress or netConfigSubnetMask are 0.0.0.0, then when the device boots, it may use DHCP to try to figure out what these values should be. If DHCP fails, before the device can talk on the network, this value must be configured (e.g., through a terminal attached to the device).

netConfigSubnetMask.name: netConfigSubnetMask
netConfigSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask of this Net interface. The default value for this object is 0.0.0.0. If either the netConfigIPAddress or netConfigSubnetMask are 0.0.0.0, then when the device boots, it may use DHCP to try to figure out what these values should be. If DHCP fails, before the device can talk on the network, this value must be configured (e.g., through a terminal attached to the device).

netConfigDefaultGateway.name: netConfigDefaultGateway
netConfigDefaultGateway.description: The IP Address of the default gateway. If this value is undefined or unknown, it shall have the value 0.0.0.0.

netConfigHttpPort.name: netConfigHttpPort
netConfigHttpPort.description: The port number for HTTP. Default value is 80.

netConfigHttpsPort.name: netConfigHttpsPort
netConfigHttpsPort.description: The port number for Secure HTTP. Default value is 443.

dot118021xState.name: dot118021xState
dot118021xState.description: This attribute indicates that the Enterprise the state of the 802.1x authentication algorithm.

dot118021xBroadcastKeyRefreshRate.name: dot118021xBroadcastKeyRefreshRate
dot118021xBroadcastKeyRefreshRate.description: The number (in minutes) between changing the broadcast key for 802.1x and WPA clients

dot118021xSessionKeyRefreshRate.name: dot118021xSessionKeyRefreshRate
dot118021xSessionKeyRefreshRate.description: The number (in minutes) between changing session keys for 802.1x and WPA clients

dot118021xReauthenticationTimeout.name: dot118021xReauthenticationTimeout
dot118021xReauthenticationTimeout.description: The number (in minutes) between forcing 802.1x clients to reauthenticate

dot11MACAuthenticationType.name: dot11MACAuthenticationType
dot11MACAuthenticationType.description: This value indicates the type of mac authentication in use.

dot11AuthenticationServerTable.name: dot11AuthenticationServerTable
dot11AuthenticationServerTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each authentication server.

dot11AuthenticationServerEntry.name: dot11AuthenticationServerEntry
dot11AuthenticationServerEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one authentication server of the AP.

dot11AuthenticationServer.name: dot11AuthenticationServer
dot11AuthenticationServer.description: This value indicates the IP address of the authentication server.

dot11AuthenticationPort.name: dot11AuthenticationPort
dot11AuthenticationPort.description: This value indicates the UDP Port used by the authentication server.

dot11AuthenticationKey.name: dot11AuthenticationKey
dot11AuthenticationKey.description: This value indicates the shared key used by the authentication server.

dot11AuthenticationRetransmit.name: dot11AuthenticationRetransmit
dot11AuthenticationRetransmit.description: This value indicates the retransmit timer length used by the authentication server.

dot11AuthenticationTimeout.name: dot11AuthenticationTimeout
dot11AuthenticationTimeout.description: This value indicates the Timeout value(sec) used by the authentication server.

dot11AuthenticationAcctPort.name: dot11AuthenticationAcctPort
dot11AuthenticationAcctPort.description: The port number for radius server accounting.

dot11AuthenticationInterimUpdate.name: dot11AuthenticationInterimUpdate
dot11AuthenticationInterimUpdate.description: This value indicates the Timeout value(sec) used by the radius server interim update.

dot11FilterDefault.name: dot11FilterDefault
dot11FilterDefault.description: This value indicates the default access for local mac filters.

dot11FilterTable.name: dot11FilterTable
dot11FilterTable.description: Table of status information about each configured MAC Address Filtering Entry.

dot11FilterEntry.name: dot11FilterEntry
dot11FilterEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one radio of the AP.

dot11FilterAddress.name: dot11FilterAddress
dot11FilterAddress.description: This value indicates the MAC address of the filter entry.

dot11FilterStatus.name: dot11FilterStatus
dot11FilterStatus.description: This value indicates the Status of the filter entry. Ifallowed, the client is allowed access to the network. If disallowed, the no frames will be forwarded to the network from the client.

dot11AuthenticationSupplicantTable.name: dot11AuthenticationSupplicantTable
dot11AuthenticationSupplicantTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of supplicant

dot11AuthenticationSupplicantEntry.name: dot11AuthenticationSupplicantEntry
dot11AuthenticationSupplicantEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one supplicant.

dot118021xSuppIndex.name: dot118021xSuppIndex
dot118021xSuppIndex.description: Index of the interface for which this supplicant is running. Currently only the ethernet interface.

dot118021xSuppState.name: dot118021xSuppState
dot118021xSuppState.description: This object is used to enable or disable the 802.1x supplicant.

dot118021xSuppUser.name: dot118021xSuppUser
dot118021xSuppUser.description: This value indicates the username for supplicant. If value is configured, will display ****. Else will display EMPTY.

dot118021xSuppPasswd.name: dot118021xSuppPasswd
dot118021xSuppPasswd.description: This value indicates the password for supplicant. If value is configured, will display ****. Else will display EMPTY.

enterpriseApAdminUser.name: enterpriseApAdminUser
enterpriseApAdminUser.description: This value indicates the username for management login.

enterpriseApAdminPassword.name: enterpriseApAdminPassword
enterpriseApAdminPassword.description: This value indicates the password for management login. Accept empty string to remove the password.

enterpriseApSecurityTable.name: enterpriseApSecurityTable
enterpriseApSecurityTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each radio in terms of security settings.

enterpriseApSecurityEntry.name: enterpriseApSecurityEntry
enterpriseApSecurityEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one radio of the AP.

enterpriseApSecurityAuthType.name: enterpriseApSecurityAuthType
enterpriseApSecurityAuthType.description: This value indicates the type of authentication in use for this radio interface.

enterpriseApSecuritySharedKeyLen.name: enterpriseApSecuritySharedKeyLen
enterpriseApSecuritySharedKeyLen.description: This value indicates the shared key length for this radio interface.

enterpriseApSecurityWPAMode.name: enterpriseApSecurityWPAMode
enterpriseApSecurityWPAMode.description: This value indicates the state of WPA for this radio interface.

enterpriseApSecurityWPAKeyType.name: enterpriseApSecurityWPAKeyType
enterpriseApSecurityWPAKeyType.description: This value indicates the type of WPA Key Management in use for this radio interface.

enterpriseApSecurityWPACipher.name: enterpriseApSecurityWPACipher
enterpriseApSecurityWPACipher.description: This value indicates the type of WPA Cipher in use for this radio interface.

enterpriseApSecurityWPAPSKType.name: enterpriseApSecurityWPAPSKType
enterpriseApSecurityWPAPSKType.description: This value indicates the type of WPA Pre Shared Key in use for this radio interface.

enterpriseApSecurityWPAPSK.name: enterpriseApSecurityWPAPSK
enterpriseApSecurityWPAPSK.description: This value indicates WPA Pre Shared Key in use for this radio interface.

enterpriseApSecurityWEPKeyType.name: enterpriseApSecurityWEPKeyType
enterpriseApSecurityWEPKeyType.description: This value indicates the type of WEP Key in use for this radio interface.

enterpriseApSecurityWEPEnabled.name: enterpriseApSecurityWEPEnabled
enterpriseApSecurityWEPEnabled.description: This value indicates whether WEP is enabled.

enterpriseApRadioTable.name: enterpriseApRadioTable
enterpriseApRadioTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each radio.

enterpriseApRadioEntry.name: enterpriseApRadioEntry
enterpriseApRadioEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one radio of the AP.

enterpriseApRadioAutoChannel.name: enterpriseApRadioAutoChannel
enterpriseApRadioAutoChannel.description: This value indicates whether auto channel selection is enabled or not for this radio interface

enterpriseApRadioTransmitPower.name: enterpriseApRadioTransmitPower
enterpriseApRadioTransmitPower.description: This value indicates the transmit power for this radio interface.

enterpriseApRadioTurboMode.name: enterpriseApRadioTurboMode
enterpriseApRadioTurboMode.description: This value indicates whether turbo mode is enabled for this radio interface.

enterpriseApRadioDataRate.name: enterpriseApRadioDataRate
enterpriseApRadioDataRate.description: This value indicates the data rate for this radio interface. Radio interface A operates at 6, 9, 12, 18, 24, 36, 48, 54. Radio interface G operates all listed data rates. The auto setting will attempt to set the best data rate for the interface

enterpriseApRadioGMode.name: enterpriseApRadioGMode
enterpriseApRadioGMode.description: This value indicates the radio mode for the 802.11g radio. This setting is only valid for the 802.11g interface.

enterpriseApRadioAntennaMode.name: enterpriseApRadioAntennaMode
enterpriseApRadioAntennaMode.description: This value indicates the antenna mode in use for the G-radio. The values are interpreted as follows: both(1) means use both built-in antennas, left(2) means use left side. right(3) means use right side. invalid(4) means not support. This setting is only valid for the 802.11g interface.

rogueApState.name: rogueApState
rogueApState.description: This value is used to enable/disable Rogue Ap Detection for this radio interface.

rogueApInterval.name: rogueApInterval
rogueApInterval.description: How often to scan for Rogue Aps. The interval in minutes, with default of 720(minutes).

rogueApDuration.name: rogueApDuration
rogueApDuration.description: How long to scan each channel (in milliseconds). A longer duration will yield more complete results. A shorter duration will allow clients a better chance of remaining connected. Default value is 350(milliseconds).

rogueApScanNow.name: rogueApScanNow
rogueApScanNow.description: When writing the value to enable, the AP will trigger the Rouge AP scan function. The value will always return disable(2).

enterpriseApVapRadioTable.name: enterpriseApVapRadioTable
enterpriseApVapRadioTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each Vap radio.

enterpriseApVapRadioEntry.name: enterpriseApVapRadioEntry
enterpriseApVapRadioEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one Vap radio of the AP.

enterpriseApVapRadioState.name: enterpriseApVapRadioState
enterpriseApVapRadioState.description: This value indicates the state of the radio interface.

enterpriseApVapRadioClosedSystem.name: enterpriseApVapRadioClosedSystem
enterpriseApVapRadioClosedSystem.description: This value indicates whether closed system is enabled for this radio interface.

enterpriseApVapRadioMaxAssoc.name: enterpriseApVapRadioMaxAssoc
enterpriseApVapRadioMaxAssoc.description: This value indicates the max number of clients allowed on this radio interface.

enterpriseApVapRadioTransmitKey.name: enterpriseApVapRadioTransmitKey
enterpriseApVapRadioTransmitKey.description: This value indicates default transmit key in use for this radio interface.

enterpriseApVapRadioDescription.name: enterpriseApVapRadioDescription
enterpriseApVapRadioDescription.description: This value indicates the description for this radio interface.

radioWdsTable.name: radioWdsTable
radioWdsTable.description: Table of configuration information for Wds for each Radio interface.

radioWdsEntry.name: radioWdsEntry
radioWdsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of peer Bridging for one radio of the AP. The table is indexed by radio Index (corresponding to enterpriseApRadioTable). The table does not contain the radio index as a member of the table.

wdsApRole.name: wdsApRole
wdsApRole.description: This value indicates the role of the Ap for this radio: normal operation(1), bridge master(2) which accepts only repeaters to associate with, repeater Ap(3) that accepts wireless station and other repeaters if it is root-connected: bridge-connected or root connected, and bridge(4) which bridges ethernet traffic to WDS parent bridge but does not relay wireless traffic.

radioWdsPeerTable.name: radioWdsPeerTable
radioWdsPeerTable.description: Table of configuration information for Wds Peers for each Radio interface.

radioWdsPeerEntry.name: radioWdsPeerEntry
radioWdsPeerEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of peer Bridging for one radio of the AP. The table is indexed by radio Index (corresponding to enterpriseApRadioTable) and the peer index (Up to 6). The table does not contain the radio index as a member of the table.

wdsPeerIndex.name: wdsPeerIndex
wdsPeerIndex.description: Peer Index for the radio interface.

rogueApDetectionTable.name: rogueApDetectionTable
rogueApDetectionTable.description: Table of each AP that has been detected.

rogueApEntry.name: rogueApEntry
rogueApEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about any AP detected.

apNotificationDot11MacAddr.name: apNotificationDot11MacAddr
apNotificationDot11MacAddr.description: Mac Address of the affected interface, returned with traps only.

apNotificationDot11Station.name: apNotificationDot11Station
apNotificationDot11Station.description: This attribute holds the MAC address of the wireless station

apNotificationDot11RequestType.name: apNotificationDot11RequestType
apNotificationDot11RequestType.description: This attribute defines the request type sent by the station. Value = 1: Unknown request type Value = 2: Association Request Value = 3: Re-association Request Value = 4: Authentication

apNotificationDot11ReasonCode.name: apNotificationDot11ReasonCode
apNotificationDot11ReasonCode.description: This attribute defines the reason for the failure of an operation. Value = 1: Invalid mode/state Value = 2: Station not authenticated. Value = 3: Internal error Value = 4: Out of sequence frame Value = 5: Un-supportd algorithm Value = 6: Invalid frame length Value = 7: WEP is required on the AP Value = 8: WEP not allowed Value = 9: Challenge text mismatch

apNotificationDot11IpAddress.name: apNotificationDot11IpAddress
apNotificationDot11IpAddress.description: This value indicates the IP address of the Access Point

apNotificationDot11AuthenticatorMacAddr.name: apNotificationDot11AuthenticatorMacAddr
apNotificationDot11AuthenticatorMacAddr.description: This attribute holds the MAC address of the authenticator for the AP.

sysSystemUp.name: sysSystemUp
sysSystemUp.description: The system up notification shall be sent when the AP is fully up and running.

sysSystemDown.name: sysSystemDown
sysSystemDown.description: The system down notification shall be sent before the AP is about to reboot.

sysRadiusServerChanged.name: sysRadiusServerChanged
sysRadiusServerChanged.description: The RADIUS server changed notification shall be sent when the RADIUS server has changed from Primary / Secondary to Secondary / Primary.

dot11StationAssociation.name: dot11StationAssociation
dot11StationAssociation.description: The associate notification shall be sent when a station successfully associates with the Access Point. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has associated.

dot11StationReAssociation.name: dot11StationReAssociation
dot11StationReAssociation.description: The re-associate notification shall be sent when a station successfully re-associates with the Access Point. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has associated.

dot11StationAuthentication.name: dot11StationAuthentication
dot11StationAuthentication.description: The authentication notification shall be sent when a station successfully authenticates with the Access Point. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

dot11StationRequestFail.name: dot11StationRequestFail
dot11StationRequestFail.description: The station request fail shall be sent out when a station fails to associate / re-associate / authenticate with the Access Point. The notification shall include the MAC address of the station and the reason code for the failure.

dot11InterfaceAGFail.name: dot11InterfaceAGFail
dot11InterfaceAGFail.description: The InterfaceAGFail notification shall be sent out when 802.11a/802.11g wireless interface has failed.

dot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess.name: dot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess
dot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess.description: The 802.1x MAC address authentication success notification shall be sent when a station successfully authenticates the MAC address with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

dot1xMacAddrAuthFail.name: dot1xMacAddrAuthFail
dot1xMacAddrAuthFail.description: The 802.1x MAC address authentication failure notification shall be sent when a station fails to authenticate the MAC address with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that failed to authenticate.

dot1xAuthNotInitiated.name: dot1xAuthNotInitiated
dot1xAuthNotInitiated.description: The 802.1x authentication not initiated notification shall be sent when a station did not initiate 802.1x authentication with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that did not initiate 802.1x authentication.

dot1xAuthSuccess.name: dot1xAuthSuccess
dot1xAuthSuccess.description: The 802.1x authentication success notification shall be sent when a station successfully authenticates with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

dot1xAuthFail.name: dot1xAuthFail
dot1xAuthFail.description: The 802.1x authentication failure notification shall be sent when a station fails to authenticate with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that failed to authenticate.

localMacAddrAuthSuccess.name: localMacAddrAuthSuccess
localMacAddrAuthSuccess.description: The Local MAC address authentication success notification shall be sent when a station successfully authenticates the MAC address with the database stored locally within the AP. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

localMacAddrAuthFail.name: localMacAddrAuthFail
localMacAddrAuthFail.description: The Local MAC address authentication failure notification shall be sent when a station fails to authenticate the MAC address with the database stored locally within the AP. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

pppLogonFail.name: pppLogonFail
pppLogonFail.description: The PPP Logon failure notification shall be sent out when the AP fails to login successfully to the PPP peer using the supplied username and password.

iappStationRoamedFrom.name: iappStationRoamedFrom
iappStationRoamedFrom.description: The IAPP Station Roamed-From Notification shall be sent out whenever a station roams from another Access Point (AP) to this AP. The notification shall include the MAC address of the station and the IP address of the old AP.

iappStationRoamedTo.name: iappStationRoamedTo
iappStationRoamedTo.description: The IAPP Station Roamed-To Notification shall be sent out whenever a station roams to another Access Point (AP) from this AP. The notification shall include the MAC address of the station and the IP address of the new AP.

iappContextDataSent.name: iappContextDataSent
iappContextDataSent.description: The IAPP Context Data Sent notification shall be sent out whenever the context data for a station has been sent to the new AP with which the station has associated. The notification shall include the MAC address of the station and the IP address of the new AP.

sntpServerFail.name: sntpServerFail
sntpServerFail.description: The sntpServerFail notification shall be sent when the AP fails to get time from the configured SNTP server.
